div.div:
Updates nutrition infographic data and visuals
Refines titles and data for bar charts representing nutrient quality and meal preparation times.
Improves labeling for better clarity and enhances color schemes for better visual appeal.
Removes outdated graphs to streamline the infographic presentation.
Relates to user feedback for clearer representations of nutritional information.
Enhances Nutrition interface with optional description and imports ChartOptions; updates title casing in nutrition infographics

Adds chart component for nutrition data visualization
Implements a new chart component to display various nutrition data types using Chart.js.
Updates the page to render the chart for each nutrition dataset fetched, enhancing the user experience with visual representation.
Improves data handling by changing the state type from Activity to Nutrition.

Adds nutrition chart interfaces and types
Implements interfaces for nutrition data visualization.
Introduces `Nutrition`, `Data`, and `ChartOptions` types to support various chart configurations.
Enhances the codebase for future nutrition-related features.

Refactors import statements in carousel component
Reorders and organizes import statements for clarity and consistency.
Ensures better readability of the code structure.
No functional changes introduced.

Removes duplicate icon import in dynamic button component
Eliminates redundant import of icons to streamline the codebase.
Improves maintainability by reducing potential confusion.
No functional changes made.

Renames nutrition tools to nutrition infographics
Changes identifiers and titles from "nutritionTools" to "nutritionInfographics" for better clarity and categorization.
Refines descriptions and adds visual elements for enhanced user engagement and understanding of nutritional concepts.

Add nutrition infographics for macronutrient breakdown, meal frequency patterns, micronutrient deficiencies, sources of added sugar, and weekly grocery cost vs. nutrition
- Created macronutrient breakdown visualizations including daily ratios, meal content, diet types, and fitness goals. - Developed meal frequency patterns charts covering distribution, age group preferences, health impacts, and productivity. - Introduced micronutrient deficiencies graphics highlighting adult deficiencies, gender prevalence, and health impacts. - Added sources of added sugar analysis with pie and bar charts on dietary contributions and age group consumption. - Implemented weekly grocery cost vs. nutrition insights comparing costs with protein, fat, vitamin intake, and meal planning success.
Add nutrition infographics layout and page components to the mental health toolkit
Remove deprecated nutrition tools and associated layout and page components from the mental health toolkit
Remove deprecated toolkits from resources, including self-compassion, sleep optimization, self-care, emotional regulation, and visualization exercises.

Remove deprecated toolkits and their associated pages from the mental health toolkit section, including self-care and discovery, self-compassion and self-esteem, sleep optimization guides, stress management tools, and visualization exercises. Update the toolkit resource file to reflect these removals.

Enhances fitness toolkit carousel functionality
Implements new carousel navigation with buttons for easier user interaction.
Refactors icon handling to improve visual representation.
Incorporates additional image display options in the gallery based on data length.
Fixes layout issues in the Masonry and Mixed galleries for better responsiveness.
Updates gallery data structure for flexibility.
Remove unused fitness collection components and Embla Carousel files
Add Embla Carousel component with navigation buttons and dot indicators

Add fitness routines for recovery, regeneration, and strength training
- Introduced a new file for recovery and regeneration routines, including active stretching, foam rolling, and breathwork exercises. - Added a comprehensive strength training file featuring various workouts targeting full-body strength, upper and lower body, and core stability. - Each routine includes detailed exercise descriptions, how-to steps, tips, sets, and repetitions to guide users effectively.
Rename fitness toolkit to fitness collection and update related imports and descriptions
Add fitness collection layout and page components with tool context integration

Adds GSAP and Embla Carousel dependencies
Implements GSAP for advanced animations and Embla Carousel for enhanced carousel functionality.
Updates package-lock and package.json to include version 3.13.0 of GSAP and version 8.6.0 of Embla Carousel.
Improves UI interactions and animations.

Refactors theme toggle component for improved performance
Memoizes toggle button content to optimize rendering. Updates accessibility labels for better user experience. Ensures proper mounting check before rendering the toggle.
Relates to UI enhancement efforts.

Adds client directive to not-found component
Enhances the not-found component by adding the "use client" directive.
This change ensures the component is rendered on the client side, improving user experience and responsiveness.
Fix optional chaining for highlights in LeadershipCard component

Refactors health articles page layout and adds image tiles
Improves the structure of the health articles page by introducing a main layout wrapper.
Includes overlapping image tiles for enhanced visual appeal and updates the styling for improved readability and user engagement.
Removes redundant elements to streamline the content presentation.
